// @test regression/INV108-nested-function-definition
// @description A function/method definition is legal only at module scope. A nested => definition inside a function body (or an if/for/while block) is TV's CE10156 "Syntax error at input '=>'", anchored at the arrow. Our parser used to accept it (piners/freedom L-006). See INV108.
// @expects parse: fail
// @expects error: line=4, column=9, message=/Syntax error at input/
//@version=6
indicator("s")
f() =>
    g() =>
        1
    g()
plot(f())
